Hormones 
\f1\b0\fs36 \cf4 \cb1 \

\f0\b \cb3 Hormones 
\f1\b0 can be secreted in the following ways: \cb1 \

\f2 \cb3 \uc0\u9679  \'a0
\f0\b Endocrine 
\f1\b0 - through the 
\f3\i bloodstream
\f1\i0 . \cb1 \

\f2 \cb3 \uc0\u9679  \'a0
\f0\b Exocrine 
\f1\b0 - through 
\f3\i ducts
\f1\i0 . \cb1 \

\f2 \cb3 \uc0\u9679  \'a0
\f0\b Paracrine 
\f1\b0 - to 
\f3\i neighboring cells
\f1\i0 . \cb1 \

\f2 \cb3 \uc0\u9679  \'a0
\f0\b Autocrine 
\f1\b0 - onto the 
\f3\i same cell 
\f1\i0 that is secreting the hormone. \cb1 \uc0\u8232 \
